ESP32 Pin Mapping for Line Maze Solver

Motor Driver Connections
    IN1 → GPIO 18 (Left Motor Forward)

    IN2 → GPIO 19 (Left Motor Backward)

    IN3 → GPIO 22 (Right Motor Forward)

    IN4 → GPIO 23 (Right Motor Backward)

Motor Encoder Connections
    Left Motor Encoder C1 → GPIO 26

    Left Motor Encoder C2 → GPIO 27

    Right Motor Encoder C1 → GPIO 32

    Right Motor Encoder C2 → GPIO 33

Line Following IR Sensors (TCRT5000 Array)
    IR 1 (Leftmost) → GPIO 34

    IR 2 (Left) → GPIO 35

    IR 3 (Center) → GPIO 13

    IR 4 (Right) → GPIO 14

    IR 5 (Rightmost) → GPIO 25

Buck Converter Connections
Buck Converter 1 (For ESP32 & Sensors)

    Input (VIN+) → Main Battery Positive

    Input (GND) → Main Battery Negative

    Output (VOUT+) → ESP32 3.3V & IR Sensors VCC

    Output (GND) → ESP32 GND & IR Sensors GND

Buck Converter 2 (For Motor Driver)

    Input (VIN+) → Main Battery Positive

    Input (GND) → Main Battery Negative

    Output (VOUT+) → Motor Driver VCC (5V)

    Output (GND) → Motor Driver GND